In terms of end users, hospitals are expected to continue dominating the market due to the escalating number of surgeries and the persistent challenge of hospital-acquired infections. The demand for infection control supplies in hospitals is projected to remain high as healthcare facilities strive to maintain high standards of hygiene and prevent the spread of infections among patients and staff. Other key end users such as clinics and ambulatory surgical centers are also likely to contribute to the market growth as they focus on implementing robust infection prevention measures.

